."},{"content":"Return boiled bagels to prepared baking sheet and bake for 8 minutes (500°F). Reduce oven temperature to 450°F then bake a further 6-8 minutes until lightly browned. Allow to cool on wire rack and serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Adding baking soda to the water alkalizes it, which helps to produce a better crust.","If you do not want to cook the bagels immediately, after they've risen: tightly wrap shaped bagels with cling wrap and refrigerate for up to 48 hours then proceed as directed by recipe.","Baked bagels can be frozen for up to a month.","Bagels are unusual in that they are boiled before baking and they also must have a very stiff dough. This produces the typical chewy texture with a good crust. The advantage of this method is that the bagels can be prepared in advance and cooked as required."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h 20m","6 pieces"]}